  /noCo/api/v1/requestLog/status/{requestId}:
    get:
      summary: Poll Status
      parameters:
        - name: x-auth-token
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: c2cccdf27ebaaefeffeedee0ca4cceb9333b4f31e676e4531cc208b9725bc330
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Poll Status
      tags:
        - AI Extraction
      description: >-
        ## 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:**  

        Check the status of an asynchronous extraction request.


        Used to monitor extraction job progress triggered from the extraction
        execution endpoint.


        ---


        ## 2️⃣ Endpoint


        ``` bash

        GET /noCo/api/v1/requestLog/status/{requestId}

         ```

        ---


        ## 3️⃣ Path Parameters


        | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | requestId | string | ✅ Yes | Request ID returned from Trigger
        Extraction endpoint |


        ---


        ## 4️⃣ Authentication


        Requires authentication using:


        ``` bash

        x-auth-token: <token>

         ```

        ---


        ## 5️⃣ Request Headers


        | Header | Required |

        | --- | --- |

        | x-auth-token | ✅ Yes |


        ---


        ## 6️⃣ Example Request


        ``` bash

        curl -X GET
        https://be.datagol.ai/noCo/api/v1/requestLog/status/{requestId} \

        -H "x-auth-token: <token>"

         ```

        ---


        ## 7️⃣ Behavior Summary


        ```

        Retrieves the processing status of an asynchronous extraction request.

        This endpoint is used for polling extraction job execution progress.

         ```
    parameters:
      - name: requestId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
  /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables:
    post:
      summary: Create Workbooks
      parameters:
        - name: x-auth-token
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: 7b6c69bd3431489e9bc79405e08fc37bb26813dcaf8ba5067808173b49282866
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - WorkBook
      description: >-
        # Create Workbook


        ## 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:**


        Creates a new Workbook inside a specified workspace.


        In the system architecture, a **Workbook is implemented as a Table
        resource**.


        This endpoint creates:


        - A new table (workbook container)
            
        - Initial column definitions
            
        - Optional metadata (description, views, position)
            
        - Table type (e.g., DYNAMIC)
            

        ---


        ## 2️⃣ Endpoint


        ```

        POST /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables

         ```

        ---


        ## 3️⃣ Path Parameters


        | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | workspaceId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Identifier of the workspace where the
        workbook will be created |


        ---


        ## 4️⃣ Authentication


        Requires **Bearer JWT Token**


        ```

        Authorization: x-auth-token <token>

         ```

        ---


        ## 5️⃣ Required Permissions


        User must have:


        - `CREATE_DATASOURCE` or equivalent table creation permission
            
        - Workspace-level write access
            

        ---


        ## 6️⃣ Request Headers


        | Header | Required |

        | --- | --- |

        | Authorization | ✅ Yes |

        | Content-Type: application/json | ✅ Yes |


        ---


        ## 7️⃣ Request Body Schema


        ```

        {  "title": "string",  "tableName": "string",  "description": "string", 
        "position": 0,  "tableType": "DYNAMIC | STATIC",  "columns": [    {     
        "name": "string",      "description": "string",      "position": 0,     
        "uiDataType": "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT | NUMBER | USER | DATE | ...",     
        "uiMetadata": {        "title": "string",        "frozen": true     
        }    }  ],  "views": []}

         ```

        ---


        ## 8️⃣ Field Descriptions


        ### Workbook-Level Fields


        | Field | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | title | string | ✅ Yes | Display name of the workbook |

        | tableName | string | ✅ Yes | Internal unique identifier |

        | description | string | ❌ | Workbook description |

        | position | number | ❌ | Ordering index in workspace |

        | tableType | enum | ✅ Yes | Type of table (e.g., DYNAMIC) |

        | views | array | ❌ | Initial view configurations |


        ---


        ### Column Definition Fields


        | Field | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | name | string | ✅ Yes | Internal column name |

        | description | string | ❌ | Column description |

        | position | number | ❌ | Column order index |

        | uiDataType | enum | ✅ Yes | UI column type |

        | uiMetadata.title | string | ❌ | Display name |

        | uiMetadata.frozen | boolean | ❌ | Freeze column in UI |


        ---


        ## 9️⃣ Example Request


        ```

        curl -X POST
        \https://be.datagol.ai/noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables \-H
        "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \-H "Content-Type: application/json" \-d
        &#x27;{  "position": 0,  "tableName": "workbook_1772105600085", 
        "description": "",  "tableType": "DYNAMIC",  "title": "Workbook 1", 
        "columns": [    {      "name": "name",      "uiDataType":
        "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT",      "uiMetadata": {        "title": "Name",       
        "frozen": true      }    },    {      "name": "notes",     
        "uiDataType": "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT",      "uiMetadata": {        "title":
        "Notes"      }    },    {      "name": "status",      "uiDataType":
        "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT",      "uiMetadata": {        "title": "Status"     
        }    },    {      "name": "assignee",      "uiDataType": "USER",     
        "uiMetadata": {        "title": "Assignee"      }    }  ],  "views":
        []}&#x27;

         ```

        ---


        ## 🔄 Behavior


        When this endpoint is called:


        1. Validate workspace access
            
        2. Validate unique `workbookName`
            
        3. Create workbook metadata
            
        4. Create physical storage structure
            
        5. Create defined columns
            
        6. Apply UI metadata
            
        7. Initialize default system fields (if applicable)
            
        8. Persist configuration
            
        9. Return created workbook object
            

        ---


        ## 🔹 Table Type Behavior


        | Type | Description |

        | --- | --- |

        | DYNAMIC | Supports computed fields, AI columns, formulas |

        | STATIC | generated from pipeline |


        ---


        ## 🔐 Special Column Types


        Example:


        | uiDataType | Behavior |

        | --- | --- |

        | SINGLE_LINE_TEXT | Basic text input |

        | USER | User reference / assignment field |

        | DATE | Date picker |

        | NUMBER | Numeric input |


        ---


        ## ✅ Successful Response Example


        ```

        {  "id": "generated-table-uuid",  "title": "Workbook 1",  "tableName":
        "workbook_1772105600085",  "tableType": "DYNAMIC",  "columns": [   
        {      "id": "column-uuid-1",      "name": "name"    },    {      "id":
        "column-uuid-2",      "name": "notes"    }  ],  "createdAt":
        "2026-02-26T13:00:00Z"}

         ```

        ---


        ---


        # 📌 Behavior Summary


        This endpoint:


        > &lt;p &gt;Creates a new Workbook  with initial column
        configuration inside a workspace.&lt;/p&gt; 
          

        It supports:


        - Custom column definitions
            
        - UI metadata configuration
            
        - Dynamic table types
            
        - Initial view setup
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                position:
                  type: integer
                tableName:
                  type: string
                description:
                  type: string
                tableType:
                  type: string
                columns:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: object
                    properties:
                      description:
                        type: string
                      name:
                        type: string
                      position:
                        type: integer
                      uiDataType:
                        type: string
                      uiMetadata:
                        type: object
                        properties:
                          title:
                            type: string
                          frozen:
                            type: boolean
                title:
                  type: string
                views:
                  type: array
                  items: {}
            example:
              position: 0
              tableName: workbook_1772105600085
              description: ''
              tableType: DYNAMIC
              columns:
                - description: ''
                  name: name
                  position: 0
                  uiDataType: SINGLE_LINE_TEXT
                  uiMetadata:
                    title: Name
                    frozen: true
                - description: ''
                  name: notes
                  position: 0
                  uiDataType: SINGLE_LINE_TEXT
                  uiMetadata:
                    title: Notes
                - description: ''
                  name: status
                  position: 0
                  uiDataType: SINGLE_LINE_TEXT
                  uiMetadata:
                    title: Status
                - description: ''
                  name: assignee
                  position: 0
                  uiDataType: USER
                  uiMetadata:
                    title: Assignee
              title: Workbook 1
              views: []
    parameters:
      - name: workspaceId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: '{{workspaceId}}'
    get:
      summary: Get All Workbooks in workspace
      parameters:
        - name: isIncludeColumns
          in: query
          schema:
            type: boolean
          example: 'true'
        - name: x-auth-token
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: c2cccdf27ebaaefeffeedee0ca4cceb9333b4f31e676e4531cc208b9725bc330
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Get workbooks in workspace
      tags:
        - WorkBook
      description: >-
        ### 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:** This endpoint retrieves a list of all Workbooks
        associated with a specific workspace. It is primarily used to populate
        workspace dashboards or to fetch structural metadata for data
        synchronization tasks.


        ### 2️⃣ Endpoint


        HTTP


        ```

        GET /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables

         ```

        ### 3️⃣ Path Parameters


        | **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required** | **Description** |  

        | **workspaceId** | UUID | ✅ Yes | Identifier of the workspace to query.
        |


        ### 4️⃣ Query Parameters


        | **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required** | **Description** |  

        | **isIncludeColumns** | boolean | ❌ No | If set to `true`, the response
        includes the full column metadata for each workbook. |


        ### 5️⃣ Authentication


        Requires a valid authentication token passed in the custom header.


        HTTP


        ```

        x-auth-token: <token>

         ```

        ### 6️⃣ Required Permissions


        User must have:


        - **READ_WORKSPACE** permissions for the specified ID.
            
        - Active membership in the workspace.
            

        ### 7️⃣ Request Headers


        | **Header** | **Required** | **Description** |  

        | **x-auth-token** | ✅ Yes | Your API authentication token. |  

        | **Accept** | ❌ No | `application/json`. |


        ### 8️⃣ Field Descriptions (Response)


        | **Field** | **Type** | **Description** |  

        | **id** | string | Unique identifier for the workbook. |  

        | **title** | string | Display name of the workbook. |  

        | **columns** | array | List of column objects (only if
        `isIncludeColumns=true`). |  

        | **tableType** | enum | Type of workbook (e.g., `DYNAMIC`, `STATIC`). |


        ### 9️⃣ Example Request


        Bash


        ```

        curl -X GET \
          "https://be.datagol.ai/noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables?isIncludeColumns=true" \
          -H "x-auth-token: <your_token_here>"

         ```

        ### 🔄 Behavior


        When this endpoint is called:


        - **Workspace Validation:** The system confirms the `workspaceId` exists
        and the user has access.
            
        - **Conditional Expansion:** If `isIncludeColumns` is `true`, the system
        performs a join or secondary lookup to fetch column definitions (names,
        types, and UI metadata).
            
        - **Sorting:** workbooks are typically returned based on their `position`
        index within the workspace.
  /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{workbookId}:
