      description: >-
        ## 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:**  

        Creates a new column inside a workbook.


        Supports multiple column types such as:


        - Text column
            
        - Number column
            
        - Date column
            
        - Other supported UI data types
            

        ---


        ## 2️⃣ Endpoint


        ``` bash

        POST /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{workbookId}/column/create

         ```

        ---


        ## 3️⃣ Path Parameters


        | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | workspaceId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Workspace identifier |

        | workbookId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Workbook identifier |


        ---


        ## 4️⃣ Authentication


        Requires authentication using:


        ``` bash

        x-auth-token: <token>

         ```

        ---


        ## 5️⃣ Request Headers


        | Header | Required |

        | --- | --- |

        | x-auth-token | ✅ Yes |

        | Content-Type: application/json | ✅ Yes |


        ---


        ## 6️⃣ Request Body Schema


        ``` json

        {
          "uiDataType": "string",
          "uiMetadata": {},
          "name": "string"
        }

         ```

        ---


        ## 7️⃣ Field Descriptions


        ### Column Configuration


        | Field | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | uiDataType | string | ✅ Yes | Column type (e.g., SINGLE_LINE_TEXT,
        NUMBER, DATE etc.) |

        | uiMetadata | object | ✅ Yes | Metadata for UI display (e.g., `{
        "title": "My Column" }`) |

        | name | string | ✅ Yes | Internal column name (snake_case recommended)
        |


        ---


        ## 8️⃣ Example Request


        ``` bash

        curl --location
        'https://be.datagol.ai/noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{workbookId}/column'
        \

        --header &#x27;x-auth-token: <token>&#x27; \

        --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \

        --data '{
          "uiDataType": "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT",
          "uiMetadata": {
            "title": "sample text"
          },
          "name": "sample_text"
        }'

         ```

        ---


        ## 9️⃣ Behavior Summary


        ``` id="behcol2"

        Creates a new workbook column.

        Supports:

        • Multiple UI data types (TEXT, NUMBER, DATE, etc.)  

        • UI metadata configuration for rendering  

        • Snake_case internal column naming  

        • Server-side validation before creation

         ```
