  /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{workbookId}/columns/{columnId}:
  put:
    summary: Update Column

    parameters:
      - name: x-auth-token
        in: header
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        description: Authentication token
        example: 7b6c69bd3431489e9bc79405e08fc37bb26813dcaf8ba5067808173b49282866

    responses:
      '200':
        description: Update Column Success

    tags:
      - WorkBook

    description: >-
        # Update Column


        ## 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:**


        Updates an existing column’s metadata and configuration within a
        specified table in a workspace.


        This endpoint supports:


        - Updating column name
            
        - Changing UI metadata (title, precision, etc.)
            
        - Modifying editability flags
            
        - Updating AI settings (enable/disable AI generation)
            
        - Updating backend data type configuration
            

        If `settings.aiSettings.enabled = true`, the column becomes an
        AI-generated column.


        If set to `false`, it behaves as a standard manual column.


        ---


        ## 2️⃣ Endpoint


        ```

        PUT
        /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{workbookId}/columns/{columnId}

         ```

        ### Path Parameters


        | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | workspaceId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Workspace identifier |

        | workbookId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Table identifier |

        | columnId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Column identifier |


        ---


        ## 3️⃣ Authentication


        Requires **Bearer JWT Token**


        ```

        Authorization: Bearer <access_token>

         ```

        ### Required Permissions


        User must have:


        - Table edit permission
            
        - Column metadata edit permission
            
        - AI configuration permission (if modifying AI settings)
            

        ---


        ## 4️⃣ Request Headers


        | Header | Value |

        | --- | --- |

        | Content-Type | application/json |

        | Authorization | Bearer token |


        Browser-specific headers are optional and not required for backend
        integrations.


        ---


        ## 5️⃣ Request Body Schema


        ```

        {  "id": "uuid",  "name": "string",  "uiDataType": "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT", 
        "backendDataType": "TEXT",  "required": false,  "uiMetadata": {   
        "title": "string",    "precision": null  },  "settings": {   
        "aiSettings": {      "enabled": false,      "prompt": "string",     
        "model": "string",      "webAccess": false    }  }}

         ```

        ---


        ## 6️⃣ Field Descriptions


        ### Core Properties


        | Field | Type | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- |

        | id | UUID | Column ID |

        | name | string | Internal column name |

        | uiDataType | enum | UI representation type |

        | backendDataType | enum | Database storage type |

        | required | boolean | Whether the field is mandatory |

        | uiMetadata.title | string | Display name in UI |

        | uiMetadata.precision | number/null | Used for numeric types |


        ---


        ### Column Behavior Flags


        | Field | Description |

        | --- | --- |

        | isDataEditable | Allows editing cell values |

        | isMetaDataEditable | Allows editing column metadata |

        | isEditable | Overall editability |

        | isDataTypeEditable | Allows data type modification |

        | isDeletable | Allows column deletion |

        | isColumnLevelFormula | Indicates formula column |

        | isDynamicFormula | Indicates dynamic computed column |

        | isSystemGenerated | System-created column |


        ---


        ### 🤖 AI Settings


        | Field | Type | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- |

        | enabled | boolean | Enables AI-generated values |

        | prompt | string | Prompt used for generation |

        | model | string | LLM model name |

        | webAccess | boolean | Enables web search capability |


        ---


        ## 7️⃣ Behavior


        ### Standard Column Update


        If:


        ```

        "aiSettings": {  "enabled": false}

         ```

        - Column behaves as manual input
            
        - No AI execution triggered
            
        - Existing values remain unchanged
            

        ---


        ### AI Column Update


        If:


        ```

        "aiSettings": {  "enabled": true}

         ```

        System may:


        1. Convert column into AI-computed column
            
        2. Trigger regeneration (depending on implementation)
            
        3. Restrict manual edits (if system enforces computed-only mode)
            

        ---


        ## 8️⃣ Example Request


        ```

        curl -X PUT
        \https://be.datagol.ai/noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{tableId}/columns/{columnId}
        \-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \-H "Content-Type: application/json"
        \-d &#x27;{  "name": "question",  "uiDataType": "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT", 
        "backendDataType": "TEXT",  "required": false,  "uiMetadata": {   
        "title": "Question"  },  "settings": {    "aiSettings": {     
        "enabled": false,      "prompt": "",      "model": "gpt-4o-mini",     
        "webAccess": false    }  }}&#x27;

         ```

        ---


        ## 9️⃣ Example Response


        ```

        {  "id": "6d9ae325-6fcd-4bd6-a732-b59e424fc095",  "name": "question", 
        "uiDataType": "SINGLE_LINE_TEXT",  "backendDataType": "TEXT", 
        "required": false,  "aiEnabled": false,  "updatedAt":
        "2026-02-19T18:25:44.010Z"}

         ```

        ---


        # 🔄 Column Update Lifecycle


        When this endpoint is called:


        1. Validate workspace access
            
        2. Validate table ownership
            
        3. Validate column existence
            
        4. Check editability flags
            
        5. Apply metadata changes
            
        6. If AI settings changed:
            
            - Update AI config
                
            - Optionally trigger regeneration
                
        7. Persist changes
            
        8. Return updated column object
            

        ---


        # ⚠️ Validation Rules


        - `name` must be unique within the table
            
        - Data type changes may be restricted if data exists
            
        - AI prompt length may be limited
            
        - Unsupported model values return validation error
            
        - System-generated columns may not be editable
            

        ---


        # 📌 Summary


        This endpoint:


        > &lt;p &gt;Updates an existing column’s metadata, data type, behavior
        flags, and AI configuration within a workspace table.&lt;/p&gt; 
          

        It supports both:


        - Standard column updates
            
        - Converting a column to or from an AI-generated column
