tags:
  - WorkBook

      description: >-
        # Delete Column


        ## 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:**


        Deletes an existing column from a specified table within a workspace.


        This operation permanently removes:


        - Column metadata
            
        - Column configuration (including AI settings, formulas, flags)
            
        - All stored data values in that column across all rows
            

        ⚠️ This action is irreversible unless a backup or soft-delete mechanism
        exists.


        ---


        ## 2️⃣ Endpoint


        ```

        DELETE
        /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{workbookId}/columns/{columnId}

         ```

        ---


        ## 3️⃣ Path Parameters


        | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | workspaceId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Identifier of the workspace |

        | tableId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Identifier of the table |

        | columnId | UUID | ✅ Yes | Identifier of the column to delete |


        ---


        ## 4️⃣ Authentication


        Requires **Bearer JWT Token**


        ```

        Authorization: Bearer <access_token>

         ```

        ---


        ## 5️⃣ Required Permissions


        User must have:


        - Table edit permission
            
        - Column delete permission
            
        - Workspace-level access
            

        If the column is:


        - System-generated → deletion may be blocked
            
        - Referenced in formulas → deletion may fail
            
        - Used in pipelines/BI models → deletion may fail
            

        ---


        ## 6️⃣ Request Headers


        | Header | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- |

        | Authorization | ✅ Yes | Bearer token |

        | Content-Type | ✅ Yes | application/json |


        Browser-specific headers (`sec-ch-ua`, `User-Agent`, etc.) are optional
        and not required for backend usage.


        ---


        ## 7️⃣ Request Body


        ❌ No request body required.


        Even though `Content-Type: application/json` is present, this endpoint
        does not require payload data.


        ---


        ## 8️⃣ Example Request


        ```

        curl -X DELETE
        \https://be.datagol.ai/noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tables/{tableId}/columns/{columnId}
        \-H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \-H "Content-Type: application/json"

         ```

        ---


        ## 9️⃣ Successful Response


        ### Option A – 204 No Content (Recommended REST Practice)


        ```

        HTTP/1.1 204 No Content

         ```

        No response body.


        ---


        ### Option B – 200 OK (If API returns object)


        ```

        {  "message": "Column deleted successfully",  "columnId":
        "ca7e8674-77c5-447c-8d5a-3afbeefcc853",  "deletedAt":
        "2026-02-26T12:00:00Z"}

         ```

        ---


        # 🔄 Deletion Lifecycle


        When this API is called:


        1. Validate workspace access
            
        2. Validate table existence
            
        3. Validate column existence
            
        4. Check:
            
            - `isDeletable` flag
                
            - `isSystemGenerated`
                
            - Dependency references
                
        5. Remove:
            
            - Column metadata
                
            - Column data from storage
                
            - AI configuration
                
            - Formula references (if applicable)
                
        6. Persist changes
            
        7. Return success response
            

        ---


        # ⚠️ Special Cases


        ### 1️⃣ AI Columns


        If the column has:


        ```

        "settings": {  "aiSettings": {    "enabled": true  }}

         ```

        Deleting it will:


        - Remove AI configuration
            
        - Stop any scheduled generation jobs
            
        - Remove generated values permanently
            

        ---


        ### 2️⃣ Formula Columns


        Deletion may fail if:


        - Other columns depend on it
            
        - BI formulas reference it
            

        ---


        ### 3️⃣ System Columns


        Columns with:


        ```

        "isSystemGenerated": true

         ```

        May not be deletable.


        ---


        # 📌 Behavior Summary


        This endpoint:


        > &lt;p &gt;Permanently deletes a column and all its associated data
        from a table within a workspace.&lt;/p&gt; 
          

        It enforces:


        - Permission validation
            
        - Dependency validation
            
        - System column protection
  /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspace_id}/folder/upload:
    post:
      summary: Upload file in workspace
      parameters:
        - name: x-auth-token
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: c2cccdf27ebaaefeffeedee0ca4cceb9333b4f31e676e4531cc208b9725bc330
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Upload file in WorkSpace
      tags:
        - Knowledge Graph
      description: >-
        ## 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:**  

        Uploads one or more files into a folder within a workspace.


        Supports multipart file upload.


        ---


        ## 2️⃣ Endpoint


        ``` bash

        POST /noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspace_id}/folder/upload

         ```

        ---


        ## 3️⃣ Path Parameters


        | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | workspace_id | UUID | ✅ Yes | Workspace identifier |


        ---


        ## 4️⃣ Authentication


        Requires authentication using:


        ``` bash

        x-auth-token: <token>

         ```

        ---


        ## 5️⃣ Request Headers


        | Header | Required |

        | --- | --- |

        | x-auth-token | ✅ Yes |


        Content-Type will be automatically set to:


        ```

        multipart/form-data

         ```

        ---


        ## 6️⃣ Request Body (Form Data)


        | Field | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | files | file | ✅ Yes | File(s) to upload. Supports multiple files
        using multipart/form-data. |


        ---


        ## 7️⃣ Example Request


        ``` bash

        curl -X POST
        https://be.datagol.ai/noCo/api/v2/workspaces/{workspace_id}/folder/upload
        \

        -H "x-auth-token: <token>" \

        -F "files=@file1.csv" \

        -F "files=@file2.csv"

         ```

        ---


