  /ai/api/v2/knowledge-graph:
    get:
      summary: Get knowledge Graph
      parameters:
        - name: file_id
          in: query
          schema:
            type: string
          example: '{{fileId}}'
        - name: limit
          in: query
          schema:
            type: integer
          example: '250'
        - name: x-auth-token
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: c2cccdf27ebaaefeffeedee0ca4cceb9333b4f31e676e4531cc208b9725bc330
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Get knowledge Graph
      tags:
        - Knowledge Graph
      description: >-
        ## 1️⃣ Overview


        **Purpose:**  

        Retrieves nodes and relationships from a knowledge graph associated with
        a specific file.


        Supports limiting the number of returned graph entities.


        ---


        ## 2️⃣ Endpoint


        ``` bash

        GET /ai/api/v2/knowledge-graph?file_id={file_id}&limit={limit}

         ```

        ---


        ## 3️⃣ Query Parameters


        | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |

        | --- | --- | --- | --- |

        | file_id | string | ✅ Yes | The ID of the file whose knowledge graph is
        to be fetched |

        | limit | number | ❌ No | Maximum number of nodes/relationships to
        return (default: 100 if not specified) |


        ---


        ## 4️⃣ Authentication


        Requires authentication using:


        ``` bash

        x-auth-token: <token>

         ```

        ---


        ## 5️⃣ Request Headers


        | Header | Required |

        | --- | --- |

        | x-auth-token | ✅ Yes |


        ---


        ## 6️⃣ Example Request


        ``` bash

        curl --location
        'https://ai.datagol.ai/ai/api/v2/knowledge-graph?file_id={file_id}&limit={limit}'
        \

        --header &#x27;x-auth-token: <token>&#x27;

         ```

        ---


        ## 7️⃣ Behavior Summary


        ``` id="behkg3"

        Returns knowledge graph data including nodes and relationships.

        Supports pagination-like control using the limit parameter.

        Default response size is 100 entities when limit is not provided.
